VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'existing video. We have some jaw-dropping humanoid robot demos and a lot more. So, let\'s jump right in. First up, this AI is super cool. It\'s called Spatial LM, and this can look at a video'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and create a 3D map of the space and identify things like walls, doors, windows, and other objects. So, here\'s an example of this in action. Notice that it can analyze this video and'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'identify pretty much everything in this room, including the walls, the furniture, and other objects. Plus, notice that it creates a 3D map of everything. So, even as you move around'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the room, the outlines of all the objects it has identified remains fixed in that spatial position. So, this is a really powerful tool with a lot of use cases such as architecture, interior design, or even autonomous driving and'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'surveillance, just to name a few examples. Really quickly, here\'s how it works. So, it takes in your input video, and then it uses a technique called master slam to basically create a 3D point cloud of your video, which looks'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'something like this. It then uses a special point cloud encoder to compress the point cloud into a smaller format for processing. The compressed data is then fed into this large language model'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that generates the 3D structural layout of the space as you can see here. The awesome thing is the output can be expressed in different formats such as structural data like this or even a 2D'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'floor plan like this or even industry standard formats like this. So this is a super useful tool. Plus the team is working to develop this tech even further. So here it says spatial LM can'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'be extended to more tasks in the future such as interacting with humans as an intelligent assistant and empowering embodied agents, in other words, robots to perform complex tasks in challenging'

[02:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environments. So because this architecture has a large language model built in, you can also potentially chat with it like a chatbot. So, for example, if you feed it with a video of a'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'bedroom, you can get it to reconstruct its layout, which it does. And then you can also get it to change the bed to king size. But note that because it has spatial awareness, it also detects that if you increase the size of the bed, the'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
